						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 20 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold deposited with the Śaṅkarappāḍiyār (guild) of Kumaramārttāṇḍapuram in Tiraimūr-nāḍu, by a merchant of the place by name Nakkaṉ Pāṇḍan, for a perpetual lamp in the temple. The former agreed to measure an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of oil every day.</p>						

						</summary>
